<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                    <head>No. 306.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Morgan</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-05-15"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 15,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 183.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information a copy of a
                            note<note n="*" xml:id="d310fn1">Printed <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>,
                            No. 341, <ref target="#pg_726">page 726</ref>.</note> from the minister
                        of Mexico here, dated the 29th ultimo, and of my reply<note n="†" xml:id="d310fn2">Printed <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>, No. 342, <ref target="#pg_727">page 727</ref>.</note> of the 4th instant,
                        concerning the killing of Capt. Emmet Crawford in Mexico recently.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>